President Trump held a bill signing event in the Roosevelt Room, where he signed H.J. Resolution 38, eliminating a regulation that he believes would have been harmful to the coal industry and American jobs. He thanked the politicians and coal miners in attendance and emphasized his commitment to getting rid of unnecessary regulations that impede economic growth. The President highlighted the importance of coal for defense and promised to fight for low-energy prices. Several politicians and coal miners spoke at the event, expressing their gratitude for the President's support and his efforts to revive the coal industry. After signing the bill, President Trump invited the attendees to a tour of the Oval Office.